        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 20 at 2:44PM CST by NWS Fort Worth TX</headline>
        <description>At 244 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles west of Chalk Mountain, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dinosaur Valley State Park around 310 PM CST.
Glen Rose and Squaw Creek Reservoir around 315 PM CST.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Chalk Mountain,
Paluxy, Johnsville, Rainbow, Selden, and Duffau.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
